<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6275] DOMCategory: text() doesn&apos;t get node value if it is a CDATA section</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6275</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DOMCategory.test() fetches nothing if data in a node is wrapped in CDATA section.&lt;br/&gt;
E.g.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &amp;lt;root&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;testText&amp;gt;text works&amp;lt;/testText&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;testCDATA&amp;gt;&amp;lt;![CDATA[cdata works]]&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/testCDATA&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/root&amp;gt;
    ....
    root.testCDATA.text() == &quot;&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems adding a check for CDATA_SECTION_NODE type should be sufficient.&lt;br/&gt;
Please find attached test and proposed fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
